FBIS4-61377 "drsov088__a94029" FBIS-SOV-94-088-A Daily Report 6 May 1994 ANNEX Azerbaijan Lezghins Reportedly Fighting in Karabakh Army Lezghins Reportedly Fighting in Karabakh Army NC0405135194 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in English 0704 GMT 4 May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY NC0405135194 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN English BFN [Text] Yerevan ("LRAGIR", "AZG" dailies), 05/04/94 -- The Azerbaijani mass media spread information on April 30, telling that Lezghin soldiers are fighting in the Karabakh Army. The RMK [Republic of Mountainous Karabakh] defense army headquarters confirmed this information, noting that indeed, 23 Lezghin volunteers have recently arrived to Stepanakert from Khachmach and Khudat districts at the north of Azerbaijan, and expressed a desire to fight against the Azerbaijani army. The commander of the Lezghin group Hajibek said, not only the fortune of Armenians but also Lezghins, Talyshs and other national minorities, whose historical lands were joined to Azerbaijan by Stalin's order, is now being solved in Karabakh.
